{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Slider · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Slider</h1>
    <p class="lead">A filled-track input for picking a value from a continuous span.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Default</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.slider</code> to an <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code>. The filled portion paints in primary; the thumb sits as a narrow vertical pill at the value's position.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="basicSlider" class="field__label">Brightness</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" id="basicSlider" value="40" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Value display</h2>
    <p>Pair with <code>&lt;output&gt;</code> for a live readout. A one-line <code>oninput</code> handler keeps the display reactive; no framework required.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-baseline">
        <label for="outputSlider" class="field__label">Opacity</label>
        <output for="outputSlider" class="text-muted-foreground">30</output>
      </div>
      <input type="range" class="slider" id="outputSlider" value="30"
             oninput="this.closest('.field').querySelector('output').value = this.value" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Min and max</h2>
    <p>Set <code>min</code> and <code>max</code> to bound the slider. Defaults to <code>0</code> through <code>100</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="minMaxSlider" class="field__label">Year</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" min="2000" max="2030" value="2026" id="minMaxSlider" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <p>Add <code>step</code> to snap the thumb to fixed increments. Drop it (or use <code>any</code>) for fully continuous movement.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="stepSlider" class="field__label">Rating</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" min="0" max="5" step="0.5" value="3" id="stepSlider" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Three sizes match the <code>.input</code> family. The thumb is shorter than the track so the clipped sliver at value extremes is less prominent, and every dimension scales with <code>--st-density</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <div class="field">
        <label for="smSlider" class="field__label">Small</label>
        <input type="range" class="slider slider--sm" id="smSlider" value="40" />
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="defaultSlider" class="field__label">Default</label>
        <input type="range" class="slider" id="defaultSlider" value="60" />
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="lgSlider" class="field__label">Large</label>
        <input type="range" class="slider slider--lg" id="lgSlider" value="80" />
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Disabled</h2>
    <p>Add the <code>disabled</code> attribute to dim the track and thumb and block interaction.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="disabledSlider" class="field__label">Playback speed</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" id="disabledSlider" value="40" disabled />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Browser validation</h2>
    <p>Native <code>:user-invalid</code> fires after the user moves the thumb past the allowed range. Usually a <code>step</code> mismatch on a constrained input. A danger border paints around the track; fill and thumb keep their brand colors.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="invalidSlider" class="field__label">Quantity (must land on a multiple of 10)</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" id="invalidSlider" min="0" max="100" step="10" value="35" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>The seeded value sits between steps. Click the thumb then click away to trip <code>:user-invalid</code>; drag to a multiple of 10 to clear it.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Server validation</h2>
    <p>Set <code>aria-invalid="true"</code> from your form library. The attribute is sticky, so the red border persists until the library clears it.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="srvSlider" class="field__label">Threshold</label>
      <input type="range" class="slider" id="srvSlider" aria-invalid="true" value="60" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How the fill works</h2>
    <p>No JavaScript. Two browser paths:</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Firefox</strong> exposes <code>::-moz-range-progress</code>, a native pseudo whose width tracks the input's value. We paint it with <code>--slider-fill</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Webkit / Blink</strong> doesn't expose a progress pseudo. The thumb gets a giant <code>box-shadow</code> (<code>-100vmax 0 0 100vmax var(--slider-fill)</code>) whose right edge lands at the thumb's right edge; <code>overflow: hidden</code> on the runnable track clips the shadow to the track shape. The shadow follows the thumb because the browser moves the thumb natively.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Ten variables retune <code>.slider</code> without touching component CSS. Override on <code>.slider</code> itself, on a parent scope, or on <code>:root</code>. The cascade scopes the change.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Use</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-h</code></td>
            <td>Track + shell height (matches <code>.input</code>)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-thumb-w</code></td>
            <td>Thumb width (narrow vertical pill)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-thumb-h</code></td>
            <td>Thumb height (centered inside track)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-thumb-gap</code></td>
            <td>Visible space between thumb's right edge and unfilled track</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-radius</code></td>
            <td>Track + thumb corner radius (pill)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-track-bg</code></td>
            <td>Unfilled segment</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-fill</code></td>
            <td>Filled segment</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-thumb-bg</code></td>
            <td>Thumb fill</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-thumb-shadow</code></td>
            <td>Thumb edge definition</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--slider-ring</code></td>
            <td>Focus halo color</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Track and thumb opt out of <code>--st-radius</code>. Pill is semantic. It isn't a style choice. Override <code>--slider-radius</code> per-component if you really want a square track.</p>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
